body:
Actually, it looks like the build did not install the protoc binary either.  It did build under my build directory (which for me is /usr/local/src/grpc/bins/opt/protobuf/protoc), however 'make install' did not copy it into /usr/local/bin or anywhere else that I can see.  To get the error above I had to manually add the build directory above to my $PATH, which I should not have to do.  Without doing that, the error I get is actually this:

```
deploy@srf-qa-02:/usr/local/src/grpc/examples/cpp/helloworld$ make
 DEPENDENCY ERROR

You don't have protoc 3.0.0 installed in your path.
Please install Google protocol buffers 3.0.0 and its compiler.
You can find it here:

   https://github.com/google/protobuf/releases/tag/v3.0.0

Here is what I get when trying to evaluate your version of protoc:

protoc --version
make: protoc: Command not found
Makefile:96: recipe for target 'system-check' failed
make: [system-check] Error 127 (ignored)


Makefile:96: recipe for target 'system-check' failed
make: *** [system-check] Error 1
```

Is this some issue with the 'install' target?

for the sake of completeness, here are the exact commands I ran on a newly-created Debian 8 VM:

```
$ cd /usr/local/src/
$ apt-get install build-essential autoconf libtool
$ apt-get install git curl
$ git clone -b $(curl -L http://grpc.io/release) https://github.com/grpc/grpc
$ cd grpc/
$ git submodule update --init
$ make
$ make install
$ which protoc
$ cd examples/cpp/helloworld/
$ make
```

Any thoughts?  This is pretty basic...

Well, here are the hacks I had to do to get the sample hello world cpp program working:
1.  Manually install protoc, since the makefile does not do it:

```
:/usr/local/src/grpc/examples/cpp/helloworld$ sudo cp ../../../bins/opt/protobuf/protoc /usr/local/bin/
```
1. Edit the helloworld/Makefile to specify additional include and lib directories

```
deploy@srf-qa-02:/usr/local/src/grpc/examples/cpp/helloworld$ git diff Makefile
diff --git a/examples/cpp/helloworld/Makefile b/examples/cpp/helloworld/Makefile
index bfb78e0..221ef06 100644
--- a/examples/cpp/helloworld/Makefile
+++ b/examples/cpp/helloworld/Makefile
@@ -30,9 +30,9 @@
 #

 CXX = g++
-CPPFLAGS += -I/usr/local/include -pthread
+CPPFLAGS += -I/usr/local/include -I../../../third_party/protobuf/src -pthread
 CXXFLAGS += -std=c++11
-LDFLAGS += -L/usr/local/lib `pkg-config --libs grpc++ grpc`       \
+LDFLAGS += -L/usr/local/lib -L../../../libs/opt/protobuf `pkg-config --libs grpc++ grpc`       \
            -Wl,--no-as-needed -lgrpc++_reflection -Wl,--as-needed \
            -lprotobuf -lpthread -ldl
 PROTOC = protoc
```
